<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9134> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9134" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 755, footnote 469" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7232> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7232" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. 53, and Procos. Africa 52. See MRR 2.228, 237. Under the decree of the Senate in 53 which prohibited the holding of a province ex praetura or ex consulatu (Dio 40.46.2), Varus must have been praetor by 54 and proconsul in Africa in 53, not 53 and 52, resp. See Caes. BC 1.31.2. Since C. Considius Longus (11) was governor of Africa after him in 52 and 51, he was probably praetor in 55 and governor of Africa already in 54. See Cic. Lig. 3-6; MRR 2.260; Sumner, Phoenix 25, 1971, 268, note 41; and Shackleton Bailey, Onom.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5909> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5909" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably still Legatus pro praetore in Spain (Flor. 2.13.75). He was defeated at sea by Didius (Flor.; Dio 43.31.3), and fell in the fighting on land (Bell. Hisp. 27.2; 31.9; Cic. Phil. 13.30; Vell. 2.55.4; App. BC 2.105; Oros. 6.16.6-8)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5827> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5827" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus pro praetore under Metellus Scipio in Africa (CIL 12.2.780ILS 5319; and cf. in 45, Flor. 2.13.75). He commanded a portion of the Pompeian fleet in Africa (Bell. Afr. 44; 62-64; 90. 1), and fled to Spain (Dio 43.30- 31; Oros. 6.16.6; cf. Auct. Bell. Hisp. 27)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5758> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5758" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Gave up his command in Africa to Metellus Scipio (see 48, Promagistrates, on Attius; and above, on Scipio), and became a Legatus pro praetore (CIL 12.2.780-ILS 5319)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5650> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5650" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He continued in command in Africa until the arrival of Metellus Scipio, Cato, and other Pompeians after their defeat at Pharsalus (see below), and at Cato's urging yielded the command to Scipio (Plut. Cat. Min. 56-57; App. BC 2.87; Dio 42.57.1; see below, on Scipio), and became a Legatus pro praetore (CIL 12.2.780-ILS 5319; see 47, Legates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5537> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5537" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "After his flight from Auximum (see Legates), he seized control of his former province of Africa (cum imperio, Caes. BC 1.31.2; imperium se habere dicebat, fasces certe habebat, Cic. Lig. 22, cf. 25, and 3), excluded Tubero from Africa (see above), and resisted Curio's attempt to capture Africa for Caesar (Caes. BC 2.23-26, and 43-44; Lucan 4.713ff.; App. BC 2.44-46; Dio 41.41-42; 42.56.2; Schol. Gron. 291 Stangl)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5271> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5271" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Had governed Africa a few years before 49 B. C. (Caes. BC 1.31.2, ex praetura eam provinciam obtinuerat). This is the latest possible date before the praetorship and governorship of Considius Longus." .
